works great in scenarios that are more CRUD (creat-read-update-delete), less in scenarios that are more convoluted with deeper logic. I personally prefer the action creators pattern because of its universal application across potential scenarios at the cost of adding more boilerplate. However, it's great to have a different pattern in hands."));
